choices.text:
Jane is faster than Joe. Joe is faster than Sam. Is Sam faster than Jane?
The answer to this question is it is not possible to tell. The information provided in the statement "Jane is faster than Joe" and "Joe is faster than Sam" does not necessarily mean that Sam is slower than Jane. It is possible for two people to have different levels of speed or for there to be other factors that affect their abilities to run at a certain pace. Without additional information or context, it is impossible to definitively answer this question.
